WEBVTT

1
00:00:31.640 --> 00:00:32.880
Shall we?

2
00:00:33.560 --> 00:00:35.200
Abso-bloody-lutely!

3
00:01:16.360 --> 00:01:19.080
Clock's ticking.
Let's get to work.

4
00:01:20.240 --> 00:01:21.880
Yes. ma'am!

5
00:01:42.480 --> 00:01:44.840
Don't mind if I do.

6
00:02:18.920 --> 00:02:21.040
Claire! They're home!

7
00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:23.440
Shit!

8
00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:34.080
I'm sure I set that.

9
00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:37.440
Bring the champagne.

10
00:02:49.640 --> 00:02:50.640
Shit!

11
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:29.136
You're a goddess!

12
00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:33.000
-Take off your clothes!
-Slow down. we have all night.

13
00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:36.240
Nicky?

14
00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:40.200
Can I be more involved
in Hillcrest?

15
00:03:40.800 --> 00:03:42.696
Why would you bring that up now?

16
00:03:42.720 --> 00:03:46.240
I just think that I can help.
and you know I'm discreet.

17
00:03:51.120 --> 00:03:53.440
Why would you ask
about Hillcrest?

18
00:03:54.080 --> 00:03:57.920
You've had all evening to bring
that up. Why bring it up now? Here?

19
00:03:58.560 --> 00:04:01.496
-Are you recording this?
-Of course not!

20
00:04:01.520 --> 00:04:03.336
Don't be crazy.

21
00:04:03.360 --> 00:04:05.240
Hey! Hey!

22
00:04:12.600 --> 00:04:15.240
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

23
00:04:43.280 --> 00:04:46.456
OK. settle down.
Question number seven.

24
00:04:46.480 --> 00:04:49.640
What is the capital of Fiji?

25
00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:51.880
That's Fiji.

26
00:04:52.400 --> 00:04:53.896
F-I-J-I.

27
00:04:53.920 --> 00:04:56.856
I was just watching a show
on this the other night.

28
00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:58.376
I know this one.

29
00:04:58.400 --> 00:04:59.736
Glenn. you said that
for every question so far.

30
00:04:59.760 --> 00:05:01.216
Of course you know them.
you set them.

31
00:05:01.240 --> 00:05:03.296
Well. I might have forgotten.
mightn't I?

32
00:05:03.320 --> 00:05:05.856
Hey. you know the rules.

33
00:05:05.880 --> 00:05:07.696
No phones in the quiz zone.

34
00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:10.080
Sorry. but I've got
to take this.

35
00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:12.456
Jordan.

36
00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:14.456
<i>Sorry to disturb
on your day off. boss.</i>

37
00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:16.416
<i>but we've had a report of a
murder at a house in Killiney.</i>

38
00:05:16.440 --> 00:05:19.320
Address belongs
to Nicholas Samson.

39
00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:24.320
-The TD? Who made the call?
-Anonymous.

40
00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:26.880
Great. OK. leave it with me.

41
00:05:28.400 --> 00:05:31.320
Apologies. but I have to go.

42
00:05:31.680 --> 00:05:35.000
-Did I hear you say TD?
-Enjoy the quiz. Mother.

43
00:05:35.400 --> 00:05:38.176
-Sorry I can't stay to help.
-Oh. don't worry. dear.

44
00:05:38.200 --> 00:05:40.600
You weren't being
very much help anyway.

45
00:05:44.880 --> 00:05:46.000
See you.

46
00:05:47.440 --> 00:05:51.640
Oh. the pressure of the
pub quiz is too much for some.

47
00:06:26.520 --> 00:06:28.296
Deputy Commissioner Mitchell.

48
00:06:28.320 --> 00:06:31.536
A house call on a Sunday?
This can't be good.

49
00:06:31.560 --> 00:06:34.776
Sorry for the inconvenience.
but it is rather important.

50
00:06:34.800 --> 00:06:37.136
This is
Chief Superintendent Wild.

51
00:06:37.160 --> 00:06:41.640
Pleasure. Chief Superintendent.
So. what's this all about?

52
00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:45.176
We've had a report
of an incident at this address.

53
00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:47.336
I'm not aware of any incidents.

54
00:06:47.360 --> 00:06:49.856
The call was about
a young woman being...

55
00:06:49.880 --> 00:06:52.360
murdered on these premises.

56
00:06:58.520 --> 00:07:01.896
Absolutely preposterous.
Who made this call?

57
00:07:01.920 --> 00:07:04.576
-It was anonymous.
-Of course it was.

58
00:07:04.600 --> 00:07:09.440
Trust me. hoax calls are par for
the course for us politicians.

59
00:07:09.800 --> 00:07:12.016
But I understand
that you have your jobs to do.

60
00:07:12.040 --> 00:07:14.256
So. what is it you need from me?

61
00:07:14.280 --> 00:07:17.056
Well. the call said the incident
took place in the master bedroom.

62
00:07:17.080 --> 00:07:20.000
-May we take a look?
-How very tiresome.

63
00:07:21.880 --> 00:07:24.640
Of course you can. This way.

64
00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:33.656
Feel free to look
wherever you want.

65
00:07:33.680 --> 00:07:35.280
I have nothing to hide.

66
00:07:35.960 --> 00:07:37.896
Is Mrs Samson home?

67
00:07:37.920 --> 00:07:40.216
Visiting her mother in Sligo.

68
00:07:40.240 --> 00:07:41.560
Oh.

69
00:07:54.840 --> 00:07:57.856
-The rug's changed.
-Excuse me?

70
00:07:57.880 --> 00:07:59.256
Charlie. what are you doing?

71
00:07:59.280 --> 00:08:01.216
There's usually
a larger rug here.

72
00:08:01.240 --> 00:08:03.416
You see these
darker floorboards?

73
00:08:03.440 --> 00:08:05.416
They haven't been
faded by the sun.

74
00:08:05.440 --> 00:08:07.416
I can't see how that's relevant.

75
00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:11.400
Good eye. Chief Superintendent.
He's quite right.

76
00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:14.536
We had a superb
Bidjar Persian rug.

77
00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:18.680
but alas. I spilled a very
nice glass of port all over it.

78
00:08:19.320 --> 00:08:22.400
Jocelyn. my wife.
was absolutely furious.

79
00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:25.776
Or maybe I'm lying.

80
00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:30.000
and I had to get rid of the rug
because it was covered in blood.

81
00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:31.640
Flump!

82
00:08:41.760 --> 00:08:44.656
What are you doing? That is not
a man with whom you mess.

83
00:08:44.680 --> 00:08:46.880
-He killed that girl.
-Can you prove that?

84
00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:49.976
Nicholas Samson is ruthless.

85
00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:53.496
He ends careers and is blatant
about it. he takes joy in it.

86
00:08:53.520 --> 00:08:56.536
You cannot take this any further
without solid. irrefutable evidence.

87
00:08:56.560 --> 00:08:58.400
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

88
00:09:20.920 --> 00:09:22.760
We have another problem.

89
00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:25.360
There was a witness.

90
00:09:29.080 --> 00:09:30.936
This dating lark is hard.

91
00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:32.816
This one want your
babies there and then. too?

92
00:09:32.840 --> 00:09:34.456
No. this one claimed to be 21.

93
00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:36.256
but was actually closer to 50.

94
00:09:36.280 --> 00:09:39.416
And when I called her on it.
she says she was 21-plus.

95
00:09:39.440 --> 00:09:41.856
but never tells anyone
what the plus is.

96
00:09:41.880 --> 00:09:44.376
Maybe you're giving off
a pheromone.

97
00:09:44.400 --> 00:09:45.696
You know Glenn.

98
00:09:45.720 --> 00:09:47.856
He's a great believer
in those things!

99
00:09:47.880 --> 00:09:49.976
I prefer not to think about Glenn
and pheromones. thank you very much.

100
00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.096
Quite right.

101
00:09:52.120 --> 00:09:54.896
Look. I don't want to worry you. but
there are two women of a certain age

102
00:09:54.920 --> 00:09:56.736
and they've been following us
for a few minutes.

103
00:09:56.760 --> 00:09:58.776
This is not funny. Harry.

104
00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:01.056
Well. perhaps
I've been around you too much

105
00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:04.640
and I'm immune to your
olfactory charms. but...

106
00:10:05.400 --> 00:10:09.280
We're definitely being stalked
by some rampant cougars.

107
00:10:09.640 --> 00:10:12.960
Shall we find out
what they want? Shall we?

108
00:10:13.440 --> 00:10:15.760
Are you following us?

109
00:10:17.080 --> 00:10:20.640
Yes. but with good reason.
We need your help.

110
00:10:21.360 --> 00:10:24.056
But if you tell anyone.
our lives could be in danger.

111
00:10:24.080 --> 00:10:26.536
It's OK. You can trust us.

112
00:10:26.560 --> 00:10:30.080
We won't tell anyone. as long as
you haven't committed a crime.

113
00:10:30.680 --> 00:10:34.240
Well. maybe just
one or two tiny ones?

114
00:10:36.040 --> 00:10:40.776
The thing is. we...
we were a little bit bored.

115
00:10:40.800 --> 00:10:43.296
So. we came up with a...

116
00:10:43.320 --> 00:10:45.056
-Well. a hobby.
-Jesus!

117
00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:47.616
If this goes slower. we'll be
cutting into wine o'clock.

118
00:10:47.640 --> 00:10:49.736
-We're burglars.
-Come again?

119
00:10:49.760 --> 00:10:53.456
We burgle houses. It's harmless.

120
00:10:53.480 --> 00:10:57.256
We never steal anything valuable
or meaningful.

121
00:10:57.280 --> 00:10:59.480
-Just trinkets.
-I like spoons.

122
00:10:59.800 --> 00:11:02.776
We know when houses nearby
are going to be empty.

123
00:11:02.800 --> 00:11:04.656
We run the Neighbourhood Watch.

124
00:11:04.680 --> 00:11:08.080
We've only done it a couple of
times. just for fun.

125
00:11:09.440 --> 00:11:12.880
-Apart from this time.
-Well. what happened this time?

126
00:11:13.400 --> 00:11:15.200
I saw a woman being murdered.

127
00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:18.520
Oh. you need to tell us
everything.

128
00:11:18.920 --> 00:11:21.576
Well. the house belongs
to Nicholas Samson.

129
00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:23.936
-The politician.
-The murdering arsehole.

130
00:11:23.960 --> 00:11:25.896
This didn't happen in Killiney
by any chance. did it?

131
00:11:25.920 --> 00:11:29.696
-Yes. how did you know?
-Uh. doesn't matter. Carry on.

132
00:11:29.720 --> 00:11:32.736
We met for some pre-burglary
drinks at mine.

133
00:11:32.760 --> 00:11:34.536
Went in over the back wall.

134
00:11:34.560 --> 00:11:36.576
crossed the lawn.
killed the alarm.

135
00:11:36.600 --> 00:11:38.560
How do you know
how to kill an alarm?

136
00:11:38.920 --> 00:11:42.376
YouTube. But we were
only just in the house

137
00:11:42.400 --> 00:11:44.456
-when he...
-The murdering arsehole!

138
00:11:44.480 --> 00:11:46.296
Came home. but he wasn't alone.

139
00:11:46.320 --> 00:11:48.760
He certainly wasn't
with Mrs Samson.

140
00:11:49.040 --> 00:11:53.496
She was American. half his age.
all legs and teeth.

141
00:11:53.520 --> 00:11:56.920
I hid under the bed. I was
absolutely crapping myself.

142
00:11:58.280 --> 00:12:01.656
She started talking about
something called Hillcrest.

143
00:12:01.680 --> 00:12:05.456
which made him angry.
and then I think he grabbed her.

144
00:12:05.480 --> 00:12:07.496
And I-I couldn't tell
what happened next.

145
00:12:07.520 --> 00:12:11.160
but he hit her with something
and then she was just...

146
00:12:12.960 --> 00:12:15.800
She was just... dead.

147
00:12:16.640 --> 00:12:17.960
What happened next?

148
00:12:18.920 --> 00:12:21.640
Well. he left the room.
went downstairs.

149
00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:24.800
And I managed to sneak out.

150
00:12:25.120 --> 00:12:27.376
I heard him on the phone
while I was leaving.

151
00:12:27.400 --> 00:12:29.696
but I couldn't hear
what he was saying.

152
00:12:29.720 --> 00:12:32.576
And then I met up with Diane.
and we went back to mine.

153
00:12:32.600 --> 00:12:35.896
We didn't know what to do.
We can't be involved.

154
00:12:35.920 --> 00:12:39.160
but we couldn't pretend
like it just hadn't happened.

155
00:12:39.520 --> 00:12:42.416
The next day. we made a call
to the Guardai.

156
00:12:42.440 --> 00:12:44.216
-Anonymously.
-Because of that call.

157
00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:47.056
Nicholas Samson will already
know that there's a witness.

158
00:12:47.080 --> 00:12:51.400
Well. that's why we can't come
forward. Will you help us?

159
00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:53.776
Go to Charlie.
see what you can get.

160
00:12:53.800 --> 00:12:55.536
I'll start with Pierce Kennedy

161
00:12:55.560 --> 00:12:58.600
and see if he's had
any Jane Does recently.

162
00:13:02.440 --> 00:13:04.776
Pierce. are you here?

163
00:13:04.800 --> 00:13:07.696
I wouldn't come any closer. I'm in
the middle of someone right now.

164
00:13:07.720 --> 00:13:10.440
I've seen a dead body before.
Plenty. in fact.

165
00:13:13.520 --> 00:13:15.256
Fair enough.
What can I do for you?

166
00:13:15.280 --> 00:13:17.840
-I'm looking for a woman.
-Aren't we all?

167
00:13:19.360 --> 00:13:21.776
Blonde. around 30.

168
00:13:21.800 --> 00:13:25.240
died of a head wound
in the past couple of days.

169
00:13:25.680 --> 00:13:28.416
No. No one like that.
I'm afraid.

170
00:13:28.440 --> 00:13:32.000
Ah. Well. if someone like that
does show up. you'd let me know?

171
00:13:32.440 --> 00:13:34.400
It'd be my pleasure. Miss Wild.

172
00:13:38.560 --> 00:13:41.600
Maybe we could
have a drink sometime?

173
00:13:44.600 --> 00:13:48.840
Actually. I. er...
I've got a lot on right now.

174
00:13:51.240 --> 00:13:52.640
Suit yourself.

175
00:14:06.720 --> 00:14:08.696
Afternoon. Chief.
You got a minute?

176
00:14:08.720 --> 00:14:11.800
Ferg! Sure. come on in.
What can I do for you?

177
00:14:13.560 --> 00:14:15.240
Can I ask you a hypothetical?

178
00:14:16.080 --> 00:14:17.480
OK.

179
00:14:17.840 --> 00:14:21.256
Let's say Harry and I
had a client or clients

180
00:14:21.280 --> 00:14:25.536
that had witnessed a crime and
were too scared to come forward.

181
00:14:25.560 --> 00:14:29.176
Could you... force me
to tell you who they are?

182
00:14:29.200 --> 00:14:31.056
This wouldn't have anything
to do with the call I got

183
00:14:31.080 --> 00:14:33.480
about a murder
in Killiney. would it?

184
00:14:34.280 --> 00:14:37.016
Doesn't take a genius.
We get an anonymous call.

185
00:14:37.040 --> 00:14:39.376
A couple of days later.
you two are hired.

186
00:14:39.400 --> 00:14:40.776
Who's the witness?

187
00:14:40.800 --> 00:14:42.376
They won't come forward.

188
00:14:42.400 --> 00:14:44.336
They're too scared
and we gave them our word.

189
00:14:44.360 --> 00:14:45.720
Hm.

190
00:14:46.080 --> 00:14:48.296
In answer to your question. yes.

191
00:14:48.320 --> 00:14:50.896
I can arrest you for perverting
the course of justice.

192
00:14:50.920 --> 00:14:54.240
You would go to prison
until you reveal what you know.

193
00:14:55.760 --> 00:14:57.296
But. of course.
I'm not gonna do that.

194
00:14:57.320 --> 00:14:58.936
Oh.

195
00:14:58.960 --> 00:15:00.376
Whoever your clients are.
they're right to be scared.

196
00:15:00.400 --> 00:15:02.096
You and Harry should be. too.

197
00:15:02.120 --> 00:15:04.856
Nicholas Samson is
a powerful. sadistic man.

198
00:15:04.880 --> 00:15:07.736
-and I believe he's a killer.
-You know him?

199
00:15:07.760 --> 00:15:09.776
He mimed beating someone
to death.

200
00:15:09.800 --> 00:15:12.936
and he'd switched a rug in
the bedroom for a smaller one.

201
00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:16.056
I'm guessing because the
original was drenched in blood.

202
00:15:16.080 --> 00:15:18.016
Does your client know
who the victim was?

203
00:15:18.040 --> 00:15:23.256
No. No name. just a description.
Blonde. about 30. American.

204
00:15:23.280 --> 00:15:26.416
Well. we've not had any missing
persons reported. I've checked.

205
00:15:26.440 --> 00:15:29.120
No Jane Does in the morgue
either. Harry checked.

206
00:15:30.120 --> 00:15:32.496
Without more evidence.
I can't pursue him.

207
00:15:32.520 --> 00:15:34.856
So. you and I never had
this conversation.

208
00:15:34.880 --> 00:15:37.600
but you find something.
you bring it to me.

209
00:15:39.240 --> 00:15:40.400
But. Ferg.

210
00:15:41.760 --> 00:15:44.080
Be very. very careful.

211
00:15:53.360 --> 00:15:56.080
-Edna says to say hi.
-Who?

212
00:15:59.840 --> 00:16:02.456
-Will you stop?
-Unlikely.

213
00:16:02.480 --> 00:16:06.496
-So. what's your good idea?
-OK. I was thinking

214
00:16:06.520 --> 00:16:09.696
that somewhere between Claire
getting out after the murder

215
00:16:09.720 --> 00:16:11.736
and Charlie and Vivian arriving.

216
00:16:11.760 --> 00:16:14.336
Samson must have arranged for
someone to come and move the body.

217
00:16:14.360 --> 00:16:17.176
That's probably who he was on
the phone with when Claire left.

218
00:16:17.200 --> 00:16:19.256
Exactly. So there's a window
of time

219
00:16:19.280 --> 00:16:21.976
where someone must have arrived
at Samson's house.

220
00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:24.576
and the house opposite happened
to have a doorbell camera.

221
00:16:24.600 --> 00:16:27.056
-So. did they give you the footage?
-Yeah. It was a very nice lady.

222
00:16:27.080 --> 00:16:29.280
Oh. older was she?

223
00:16:30.320 --> 00:16:34.776
-Unfortunately. that is where my great idea falls down.
-Oh.

224
00:16:34.800 --> 00:16:37.096
As you can see.
look. the angle's all wrong.

225
00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:39.336
You don't even see
Samson's gate.

226
00:16:39.360 --> 00:16:42.496
Cars driving by. yeah. sure.
but there's no real way

227
00:16:42.520 --> 00:16:45.176
of knowing if any of them
stopped at Samson's house.

228
00:16:45.200 --> 00:16:47.440
Bugger!
It was a great idea. though.

229
00:16:47.800 --> 00:16:48.840
Thanks.

230
00:16:52.200 --> 00:16:54.136
-How was the date. son?
-Oh.

231
00:16:54.160 --> 00:16:56.240
I'd rather not talk about it.

232
00:16:56.960 --> 00:16:59.496
-That bad. huh?
-Yeah.

233
00:16:59.520 --> 00:17:01.800
Don't give up. Ferg.

234
00:17:02.120 --> 00:17:05.840
The only time we fail
is when we give up.

235
00:17:06.480 --> 00:17:08.736
-That's what I always say.
-What?

236
00:17:08.760 --> 00:17:11.040
I've never heard you say that.

237
00:17:11.840 --> 00:17:14.536
Well. I'm saying it now.

238
00:17:14.560 --> 00:17:18.536
Actually. I'm thinking of
getting back in the game myself.

239
00:17:18.560 --> 00:17:21.760
Oh. Got anyone in mind.
have you there. Da?

240
00:17:22.600 --> 00:17:24.136
Actually. there is someone.

241
00:17:24.160 --> 00:17:27.200
but not really ready
to talk about it just yet.

242
00:17:27.920 --> 00:17:30.256
I figure the lucky lady
should be the first to hear.

243
00:17:30.280 --> 00:17:31.640
OK.

244
00:17:37.920 --> 00:17:39.656
"Politician Nicholas Samson

245
00:17:39.680 --> 00:17:42.696
has today announced a major new
development in Leopardstown

246
00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:45.256
to combat
Dublin's housing crisis.

247
00:17:45.280 --> 00:17:47.736
The Hillcrest project will break
ground in the next week.

248
00:17:47.760 --> 00:17:50.336
led by Fitzgilbert Construction.

249
00:17:50.360 --> 00:17:51.976
A spokesperson
for the government said

250
00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:53.976
that Fitzgilbert Construction
had impressed

251
00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:56.160
"with their
forward-thinking vision."

252
00:17:58.240 --> 00:18:00.056
Here. buy this for me.
will you. Da?

253
00:18:00.080 --> 00:18:01.336
Yeah.

254
00:18:01.360 --> 00:18:03.160
See ya later. son.

255
00:18:17.760 --> 00:18:19.256
I was just thinking about you.

256
00:18:19.280 --> 00:18:21.040
Great minds.

257
00:18:21.640 --> 00:18:24.136
I was wondering
if you fancied...

258
00:18:24.160 --> 00:18:26.776
-getting together. like?
<i>-Great minds indeed.</i>

259
00:18:26.800 --> 00:18:28.776
I was going to ask you
the same thing.

260
00:18:28.800 --> 00:18:31.080
There's something
I want to talk to you about.

261
00:18:31.680 --> 00:18:33.896
And there's something
I want to talk to you about.

262
00:18:33.920 --> 00:18:37.800
-Say six o'clock in the Goose?
<i>-It's a date.</i>

263
00:18:40.800 --> 00:18:42.640
Better get a new suit.

264
00:18:46.720 --> 00:18:49.896
I scanned the doorbell cam
footage again and found this.

265
00:18:49.920 --> 00:18:51.816
Fitzgilbert Construction.

266
00:18:51.840 --> 00:18:54.176
That van was seen near Samson's
house the night of the murder.

267
00:18:54.200 --> 00:18:57.336
And now. three days later. the
company's awarded a huge contract?

268
00:18:57.360 --> 00:18:59.616
Well done. you.

269
00:18:59.640 --> 00:19:02.640
But that's not proof.
We need more.

270
00:19:22.120 --> 00:19:25.800
-And there it is.
-Do you see what I see?

271
00:19:26.600 --> 00:19:30.600
-Depends. What do you see?
-The doorbell cam.

272
00:19:31.040 --> 00:19:34.336
The builder's van was following
a very nice-looking Merc.

273
00:19:34.360 --> 00:19:36.616
Just like
that nice-looking Merc.

274
00:19:36.640 --> 00:19:40.040
Yeah. you're right.
Well spotted.

275
00:19:41.640 --> 00:19:45.440
Well. look what we have
here. Who are these guys?

276
00:20:01.400 --> 00:20:03.000
Oh. er...

277
00:20:11.800 --> 00:20:13.576
Which one do we follow?

278
00:20:13.600 --> 00:20:16.640
The employee probably did the
dirty work. let's follow him.

279
00:20:58.920 --> 00:21:02.040
Now what? That might be him
done for the day.

280
00:21:02.240 --> 00:21:05.360
Unless Nicholas Samson
kills anyone else tonight.

281
00:21:16.800 --> 00:21:18.176
Go!

282
00:21:18.200 --> 00:21:20.056
Go after him.
Keep him in your sight.

283
00:21:20.080 --> 00:21:22.656
-Call me if he's coming back.
-Why. what are you gonna do?

284
00:21:22.680 --> 00:21:24.840
Go before you lose him!

285
00:21:49.840 --> 00:21:53.056
-I can help with that.
-Jesus! What are you doing here?

286
00:21:53.080 --> 00:21:54.816
I've been following you.

287
00:21:54.840 --> 00:21:57.120
I'm not very good
at sitting around and waiting.

288
00:21:57.520 --> 00:21:58.936
It's a character flaw. I know.

289
00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:01.240
It's just I have experience
with...

290
00:22:01.760 --> 00:22:04.160
Oh. so do you.

291
00:22:04.640 --> 00:22:06.640
Well. we can't hang around here.

292
00:22:10.280 --> 00:22:12.456
This isn't smart. Claire.
These people are dangerous.

293
00:22:12.480 --> 00:22:15.640
I know. Harry.
I was in the room. remember?

294
00:22:15.840 --> 00:22:19.400
Ah! Tadhg Ferrell.
We have a name.

295
00:22:53.680 --> 00:22:56.176
That's the rug from the bedroom.

296
00:22:56.200 --> 00:22:58.600
What? No one's that stupid!

297
00:23:02.440 --> 00:23:04.040
Turns out they are.

298
00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:08.080
He's on his way back.
We have to leave.

299
00:23:24.280 --> 00:23:27.576
-Where'd you come from?
-She's been following us.

300
00:23:27.600 --> 00:23:30.336
-Sorry.
-Well. what about you?

301
00:23:30.360 --> 00:23:31.816
You haven't been gone long.

302
00:23:31.840 --> 00:23:34.216
Well. he ran
to the back of some shops.

303
00:23:34.240 --> 00:23:36.536
met someone.
gave him some money.

304
00:23:36.560 --> 00:23:39.056
I know him from somewhere.
but I just can't place him.

305
00:23:39.080 --> 00:23:41.840
Well. we found something.
We need to talk to Charlie.

306
00:23:43.160 --> 00:23:44.240
OK.

307
00:23:55.520 --> 00:23:57.440
Sure one can't hurt.

308
00:23:59.400 --> 00:24:02.576
Jesus. Mother! Since when
do you know how to pick a lock?

309
00:24:02.600 --> 00:24:04.456
Harry gave me his picks
when he left.

310
00:24:04.480 --> 00:24:06.736
and Skeevy gave us a crash
course on how to use them.

311
00:24:06.760 --> 00:24:08.656
OK. I'm gonna forget that bit
right now.

312
00:24:08.680 --> 00:24:11.136
You need to persuade
your clients to come in

313
00:24:11.160 --> 00:24:12.936
and make an official statement.

314
00:24:12.960 --> 00:24:16.360
They won't. And I can't. with
good conscience. suggest it.

315
00:24:17.280 --> 00:24:20.456
You really think that you can protect
them from someone like Samson?

316
00:24:20.480 --> 00:24:23.336
And we already know he has
people to do his dirty work for him.

317
00:24:23.360 --> 00:24:25.440
Our best bet is to get
this guy to talk.

318
00:24:26.760 --> 00:24:28.896
OK. so.
who are we talking about?

319
00:24:28.920 --> 00:24:30.416
His name is Tadhg Farrell.

320
00:24:30.440 --> 00:24:32.376
and he works
for Fitzgilbert Construction.

321
00:24:32.400 --> 00:24:34.216
Why do I know that name?

322
00:24:34.240 --> 00:24:36.416
Samson just awarded them
a massive contract

323
00:24:36.440 --> 00:24:38.176
to build 1.000 houses.

324
00:24:38.200 --> 00:24:39.656
And after he killed this woman.

325
00:24:39.680 --> 00:24:42.416
Samson called Cian Fitzgilbert.
the boss.

326
00:24:42.440 --> 00:24:45.136
Now. Fitzgilbert and Farrell
went over to Samson's house.

327
00:24:45.160 --> 00:24:46.816
rolled the dead woman
up in the rug.

328
00:24:46.840 --> 00:24:48.816
and Farrell
dumped her body somewhere.

329
00:24:48.840 --> 00:24:51.120
He wasn't the brightest.
He kept the rug.

330
00:24:51.480 --> 00:24:54.576
And if you can get him
before he disposes of it.

331
00:24:54.600 --> 00:24:57.536
it will link him to Samson.

332
00:24:57.560 --> 00:25:00.416
And you're not investigating
Samson directly.

333
00:25:00.440 --> 00:25:02.416
I hear you. I like this.

334
00:25:02.440 --> 00:25:06.456
but I need probable cause to get
into this Farrell guy's house.

335
00:25:06.480 --> 00:25:10.160
Well. you can just say that
you heard reports of a break-in.

336
00:25:14.960 --> 00:25:16.440
Jordan?

337
00:25:17.720 --> 00:25:20.856
-Yes. boss.
-Had a report of a break-in

338
00:25:20.880 --> 00:25:22.936
at the house of
a man called Tadhg Farrell.

339
00:25:22.960 --> 00:25:24.536
You and me are going
to check it out.

340
00:25:24.560 --> 00:25:25.960
We are?

341
00:25:42.280 --> 00:25:44.256
I just spoke to Charlie.

342
00:25:44.280 --> 00:25:47.496
Tadhg Farrell got rid
of the rug before he got there.

343
00:25:47.520 --> 00:25:48.880
Now what?

344
00:25:50.640 --> 00:25:53.176
-Hiya. Harry. Hiya. love.
-Hey!

345
00:25:53.200 --> 00:25:55.696
-Your da here?
-Not seen him.

346
00:25:55.720 --> 00:25:57.896
-Oh.
-OK. Paula?

347
00:25:57.920 --> 00:26:01.096
-Well. you look anxious.
-Bloody hell. Harry.

348
00:26:01.120 --> 00:26:03.280
It is impossible
to keep secrets around you.

349
00:26:04.800 --> 00:26:08.056
There is something. but I need
to tell your dad first. OK?

350
00:26:08.080 --> 00:26:11.040
-OK.
-He should be here soon.

351
00:26:12.760 --> 00:26:15.040
PAULA!

352
00:26:20.800 --> 00:26:22.440
Do you get it?

353
00:26:24.040 --> 00:26:27.560
I'm the fella in that play that we
saw that time. do you remember?

354
00:26:28.920 --> 00:26:30.760
You bought the tickets for it.

355
00:26:31.320 --> 00:26:33.280
That was a brilliant night out.
wasn't it?

356
00:26:34.880 --> 00:26:36.280
What's it called again?

357
00:26:36.960 --> 00:26:39.336
Something. something.
something. something.

358
00:26:39.360 --> 00:26:42.040
-<i>A Streetcar Named Desire.</i>
-That's the one.

359
00:26:43.160 --> 00:26:45.056
It was brilliant. wasn't it?

360
00:26:45.080 --> 00:26:48.816
-We had a great time...
-Don't fucking touch me. Malky!

361
00:26:48.840 --> 00:26:50.456
We didn't!

362
00:26:50.480 --> 00:26:52.840
You spilled your drink
on the woman in front of us.

363
00:26:54.080 --> 00:26:56.680
-Did I?
-Yeah. you did.

364
00:26:57.120 --> 00:26:59.800
There were people
from my work there.

365
00:27:00.920 --> 00:27:02.680
I can't do this.

366
00:27:03.720 --> 00:27:05.440
I'm so sorry. Ferg.

367
00:27:13.320 --> 00:27:14.680
Fuck's sake. Da!

368
00:27:15.720 --> 00:27:16.960
I'm sorry. son. I...

369
00:27:20.360 --> 00:27:21.976
I don't know
what I was thinking.

370
00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:24.016
I have to make sure
she's all right.

371
00:27:24.040 --> 00:27:25.800
No. Um...

372
00:27:28.120 --> 00:27:30.240
This needs to be me. Fergus.

373
00:27:40.920 --> 00:27:42.040
Paula.

374
00:27:43.720 --> 00:27:45.336
No.

375
00:27:45.360 --> 00:27:46.960
NO?

376
00:27:47.800 --> 00:27:49.800
I was going to tell you tonight.

377
00:27:50.280 --> 00:27:52.696
Felt I owed it to you
to tell you first.

378
00:27:52.720 --> 00:27:56.000
Me and Paula have been seeing
each other for a while now. Malky.

379
00:27:56.560 --> 00:27:59.496
-And I've asked her to marry me.
-And I've accepted.

380
00:27:59.520 --> 00:28:01.240
You can't be serious.

381
00:28:02.880 --> 00:28:04.776
He threatened to break
our daughter's arm.

382
00:28:04.800 --> 00:28:07.456
I know that. Fergus told me.

383
00:28:07.480 --> 00:28:09.880
And I would never
have done that.

384
00:28:10.920 --> 00:28:14.136
That was only to motivate you
to pay me.

385
00:28:14.160 --> 00:28:17.536
But you look at me now.
turning over a new leaf.

386
00:28:17.560 --> 00:28:20.120
No more sharking.
No more anything.

387
00:28:21.400 --> 00:28:24.976
Because I'm going to make Paula
the happiest woman ever.

388
00:28:25.000 --> 00:28:27.600
-Aw.
-Because I love her.

389
00:28:29.800 --> 00:28:31.880
And I've never done that before.

390
00:28:32.280 --> 00:28:35.616
I wanted to tell you first.
out of respect. which...

391
00:28:35.640 --> 00:28:38.360
is something you've hardly
ever shown me.

392
00:28:38.920 --> 00:28:40.840
It's really Fergus
I need to tell.

393
00:28:41.920 --> 00:28:43.880
You want to come with me. Nigel?

394
00:28:44.760 --> 00:28:46.200
Of course.

395
00:29:01.160 --> 00:29:04.536
-What a bloody moron!
-I know. and I apologise.

396
00:29:04.560 --> 00:29:07.496
You're right. it was stupid.
but he's got rid of the rug now

397
00:29:07.520 --> 00:29:09.600
and it won't be found.
I guarantee it.

398
00:29:11.240 --> 00:29:13.280
But it was actually
a good thing.

399
00:29:13.760 --> 00:29:15.896
Tadhg spoke to his man
in the station.

400
00:29:15.920 --> 00:29:17.376
One of the people involved

401
00:29:17.400 --> 00:29:19.680
is the Chief Superintendent's
mother.

402
00:29:20.400 --> 00:29:23.536
-Why would she be involved?
-She's a private investigator.

403
00:29:23.560 --> 00:29:25.880
Her name's Harry Wild.

404
00:29:26.520 --> 00:29:29.136
I think
whoever was in your house

405
00:29:29.160 --> 00:29:30.936
hired her
to prove what happened.

406
00:29:30.960 --> 00:29:32.776
How is that a good thing?

407
00:29:32.800 --> 00:29:35.976
Because they'll lead us
to whoever hired them.

408
00:29:36.000 --> 00:29:38.080
and then we make the problem
go away.

409
00:29:48.440 --> 00:29:50.040
Harry Wild?

410
00:29:56.640 --> 00:30:00.160
Nice little houses. these.
Good location.

411
00:30:02.040 --> 00:30:04.696
I suspect they're not grand
enough for someone like you.

412
00:30:04.720 --> 00:30:08.000
-Mr Samson.
-So. you know who I am?

413
00:30:09.600 --> 00:30:11.376
What do you want?

414
00:30:11.400 --> 00:30:13.136
We've had a developer put in
a bid to buy the park here.

415
00:30:13.160 --> 00:30:15.120
put up a tower block.

416
00:30:15.600 --> 00:30:17.576
Thought I'd come and take a look
for myself.

417
00:30:17.600 --> 00:30:20.256
I'm sure nothing like that's
going to happen here.

418
00:30:20.280 --> 00:30:21.776
Oh. I don't know.

419
00:30:21.800 --> 00:30:24.000
There is a housing crisis
in Dublin. after all.

420
00:30:25.280 --> 00:30:28.600
What was her name? The blonde?

421
00:30:30.000 --> 00:30:32.960
I'm sure I don't know
what you're talking about.

422
00:30:34.160 --> 00:30:35.616
I'd better get on.

423
00:30:35.640 --> 00:30:37.840
No rest for the wicked.

424
00:30:48.120 --> 00:30:49.696
Hey.

425
00:30:49.720 --> 00:30:53.120
I'm sorry. Didn't mean
to sneak up on you. You OK?

426
00:30:53.640 --> 00:30:56.656
-I just met Samson.
-What? He was here?

427
00:30:56.680 --> 00:30:58.736
We have met some ugly people
in our time.

428
00:30:58.760 --> 00:31:02.496
but I've never met anyone so sure
he's going to get away with murder.

429
00:31:02.520 --> 00:31:04.016
We have to get him. Fergus.

430
00:31:04.040 --> 00:31:06.280
Well. I think I might have
identified the victim.

431
00:31:13.560 --> 00:31:16.296
-That's her.
-Her name is...

432
00:31:16.320 --> 00:31:19.016
was Cassie Forbes.

433
00:31:19.040 --> 00:31:21.096
She worked at Samson's office.

434
00:31:21.120 --> 00:31:23.216
We called the office
asking to speak to her.

435
00:31:23.240 --> 00:31:25.016
but they told us
she'd gone travelling.

436
00:31:25.040 --> 00:31:26.736
Yeah. no one seems to know
where.

437
00:31:26.760 --> 00:31:28.936
That's good she has a name now.

438
00:31:28.960 --> 00:31:31.936
Well. knowing who she was
doesn't get us any nearer

439
00:31:31.960 --> 00:31:34.096
to proving
that Samson killed her.

440
00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:37.496
We'll stay on him.
but you ladies

441
00:31:37.520 --> 00:31:40.536
might want to think about
taking a trip for a week or two?

442
00:31:40.560 --> 00:31:43.920
We can't just run away.
We've lives.

443
00:31:44.480 --> 00:31:47.216
Well. I don't really have
anything on this week.

444
00:31:47.240 --> 00:31:48.800
Or next.

445
00:31:49.560 --> 00:31:51.160
Well. we'll think about it.

446
00:31:51.520 --> 00:31:54.680
We can't hide for ever. Harry.
We need a solution.

447
00:31:55.360 --> 00:31:58.560
Well. I promise you
we're working on it.

448
00:32:04.000 --> 00:32:07.416
I don't think we've ever had
a case quite like this one.

449
00:32:07.440 --> 00:32:10.736
We know exactly what happened.
we just have no way to prove it.

450
00:32:10.760 --> 00:32:13.840
Yeah. the man is going to get
away with murder because of it.

451
00:32:14.040 --> 00:32:16.816
I think Tadhg Farrell's
the weak link here.

452
00:32:16.840 --> 00:32:18.656
Samson's the killer.

453
00:32:18.680 --> 00:32:20.336
Fitzgilbert
has too much to gain.

454
00:32:20.360 --> 00:32:22.376
Tadhg. he's just a dogsbody.

455
00:32:22.400 --> 00:32:25.040
But he's a big.
scary looking dogsbody.

456
00:32:33.920 --> 00:32:35.696
I know where I saw him.

457
00:32:35.720 --> 00:32:37.536
your man who Tadhg met
on his run.

458
00:32:37.560 --> 00:32:38.896
Who is he?

459
00:32:38.920 --> 00:32:40.096
The janitor
in Charlie's station.

460
00:32:40.120 --> 00:32:41.776
-What. are you sure?
-Absolutely.

461
00:32:41.800 --> 00:32:43.576
I mean. no one pays
any attention to the cleaner.

462
00:32:43.600 --> 00:32:46.496
He's always just emptying bins
or sweeping up.

463
00:32:46.520 --> 00:32:49.176
-We need to tell Charlie.
-Well. hold on.

464
00:32:49.200 --> 00:32:51.016
If he's passing on information
about us.

465
00:32:51.040 --> 00:32:53.176
then he knows about us

466
00:32:53.200 --> 00:32:55.656
and that's how Samson knew
where to find you.

467
00:32:55.680 --> 00:32:56.936
And if they know about us.

468
00:32:56.960 --> 00:32:58.960
-that will lead them to...
-Claire.

469
00:33:06.280 --> 00:33:09.280
I mean. he has his own
Wikipedia page. for God's sake.

470
00:33:09.560 --> 00:33:11.136
How would he even know
who we are?

471
00:33:11.160 --> 00:33:12.896
A man like that has connections.

472
00:33:12.920 --> 00:33:15.336
You're not wrong.

473
00:33:15.360 --> 00:33:17.696
Who are you?
Get out of my house.

474
00:33:17.720 --> 00:33:21.096
I'm not the one that went to call
the fucking Guardai now. am I. love?

475
00:33:21.120 --> 00:33:22.816
Are you going to kill us?

476
00:33:22.840 --> 00:33:24.696
Trust me. I don't want to do it
any more than you do.

477
00:33:24.720 --> 00:33:26.456
Well. seeing as we're the ones
who'll be dead.

478
00:33:26.480 --> 00:33:29.200
I don't think
that's an argument you can win.

479
00:33:30.040 --> 00:33:32.016
Are you for real?

480
00:33:32.040 --> 00:33:33.840
Very. Are you?

481
00:33:37.960 --> 00:33:40.336
What's the plan?
Out of interest.

482
00:33:40.360 --> 00:33:43.256
You should know. the Guardai are already
on their way. so you'd better think fast.

483
00:33:43.280 --> 00:33:45.456
And they know it's you
because we took a little video

484
00:33:45.480 --> 00:33:47.576
through the window
and we sent it to them.

485
00:33:47.600 --> 00:33:51.376
-What do you think you're doing?
-You gonna shoot all four of us?

486
00:33:51.400 --> 00:33:54.336
Oh. and then. what.
immediately go on the run?

487
00:33:54.360 --> 00:33:56.296
Be smart. fella. huh?

488
00:33:56.320 --> 00:33:58.296
OK. so far. the only thing
you're guilty of

489
00:33:58.320 --> 00:34:00.376
is disposing of a body.
but you do this.

